  "prompt": "Why do Yaz birth control pills cause weight loss?",
  "response": "Yaz birth control pills are not typically associated with weight loss. In fact, weight gain is a more commonly reported side effect of Yaz and other hormonal contraceptives. The hormones in Yaz, which include drospirenone (a progestin) and ethinyl estradiol (an estrogen), can cause fluid retention and increased appetite in some individuals, leading to weight gain.\n\nIf you or someone you know experiences weight loss while taking Yaz, it could be due to factors unrelated to the medication itself, such as changes in diet, increased physical activity, or other health conditions. It's important to consult a healthcare provider if you have concerns about weight changes or any other side effects while taking Yaz or any other medication.",
